  <title>Quiet Power Workbook 2 — FILTER: How You Filter the Noise</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Quiet Power Workbook 2 — FILTER: How You Filter the Noise. A workbook about deciding what stays, what goes, and what never gets into your mental space.">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>
<body>

<header class="site-header">
  <!-- reuse your global header / nav -->
</header>

<main class="page">

  <section class="page-hero-intro">
    <p class="book-tag">WORKBOOK 2</p>
    <h1>FILTER: How You Filter the Noise</h1>
    <p>
      A Quiet Power workbook about selection: deciding what stays, what goes,
      and what never gets into your mental space in the first place.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <h2>What this workbook is for</h2>
    <p>
      If Workbook 1 is about noticing your reactions, Workbook 2 is about the next level of the Quiet Power system:
      selection. You cannot control everything that exists, but you can control what you let close.
    </p>
    <p>
      This workbook helps you choose your inputs on purpose — what you keep, what you remove,
      and what you stop allowing into your head, calendar, and attention.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <h2>What’s inside</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Pages to map the sources of noise in your day and what they cost you.</li>
      <li>Prompts to decide what you will no longer track, answer, or carry.</li>
      <li>Space to design simple filters for media, people, work, and routines.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section page-section--cta">
    <h2>Download the workbook</h2>
    <p>
      This workbook is free to download as a PDF.
      Use it next to Workbook 1 to move from reaction to deliberate selection.
    </p>
    <div class="book-actions">
      <a href="/downloads/quiet-power-workbook-2.pdf" class="btn-primary" target="_blank">Download free PDF</a>
      <a href="/quiet-power.html" class="btn-secondary">Back to Quiet Power</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>

